   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>The eleventh year of the Emperor Caesar Domitian Augustus Germanicus, the month Kaisarios, 1 to 10. We, Komon and associates, public sitologoi of the village of Philopator, have received of the crop of the same year by leveled public . . . wheat-measure, for private land at Bacchias, (to the account of) Petalos, son of Apollonios, through Apollonous, four and one-half and one-third and one-twenty-fourth &lt;artabai&gt;, (and) for epibole, two and one-half and one-third and one-twelfth, equal for the receipt 7 2/3 1/8 artabai of wheat, and the extra charges.</ab>
         </div>
